title: Files are downloaded but not handled
body: In the download.sh file, the Rfam.full_region.gz and the rfam_annotations.tsv.gz are downloaded. However in the curate.sh file, there is no code to handle these files. So, when running update.sh these files are just left there. Are they not needed or was there supposed to be code to handle these files?

title: Error: [blastdbcmd] Skipped SEQ_ACCESSION
body:
I am facing the error:
Error: [blastdbcmd] Skipped SEQ_ACCESSION
67532 (!) times, when running:
path/to/rMSA/bin/blastdbcmd -db path/to/rMSA/database/nt -entry_batch tmp/user/rMSA_38167_200247988/rfam2.0.list.split.aa -out /tmp/user/rMSA_38167_200247988/rfam2.0.db.aa

What could have gone wrong? Thank you!

title: Empty alignment file
body:
I am receiving an empty alingment file (only the query sequence is in the file), which means that alignment was not successful.

In the running log I noticed three errors:

1) Error: [blastdbcmd] Skipped SEQ_ACCESSION - Has already been solved in another issue and it is [not an actual error](https://github.com/pylelab/rMSA/issues/4).
2) Error: Failed to open target sequence database /tmp/user/rMSA_38167_200247988/db for reading
3) sort: write error

Could you please help me?
